Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:05 PM Defendant Timothy L Mann Sr. appeared by video, in custody from the Vilas County Jail.  Attorney Dennis G Brown in court for State of Wisconsin. State speaks to the warrant being issued. Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint. Court reads charges. Attorney rights given. State speaks to bond. Court orders $500.00 signature bond with conditions: Maintain a current address with COC Office and Registry, also continue to follow up with Arbor Health and attempting to get accepted. Bond form. Court quashes warrant.
Initial appearance scheduled for December 12, 2022 at 11:00 am.
